article.headline: UNLV 75, TCU 66
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Michael Umeh scored a season-high 22 points for UNLV, which beat TCU 75-66 on Saturday night. Wink Adams added 18 points for the Runnin' Rebels (16-4, 3-2 Mountain West) and Joe Darger had 12. Umeh was 6-of-13 from the field, including 3-of-5 from 3-point range. He hit 7-of-9 free throws. TCU (10-7, 2-3) was led by Alvardo Parker, who had his first double-double with 20 points and 13 rebounds. Kevin Langford scored 14 points for the Horned Frogs, and Brent Hackett had 11. The Frogs were plagued by 23 turnovers, which translated into 36 points for UNLV. UNLV took a 40-29 halftime lead. The Runnin' Rebels played without Kevin Kruger and Wendell White, who were injured.
